OVERVIEW

OPERATING INCOME OF $465 MILLION IN 2008 WAS $554 MILLION, OR 54%, LOWER THAN OPERATING INCOME IN 2007, PRIMARILY

REFLECTING AN INCREASE IN THE COST OF CATASTROPHES. ALSO CONTRIBUTING TO THE DECLINE IN 2008 WERE THE IMPACT OF A REDUCTION IN NET INVESTMENT INCOME, AN INCREASE IN NON-CATASTROPHE RELATED

WEATHER LOSSES AND LOSS COST TRENDS. THE COST OF CATASTROPHES IN 2008 TOTALED $618 MILLION, COMPARED

87

