CHANGES IN THE ADMINISTRATIVE POLICIES OF SECOND INJURY FUNDS

(1)

THESE

ARE ADMINISTRATIVE BODIES THAT EVALUATE WHETHER OR NOT A GIVEN CLAIM FOR WORKERS' COMPENSATION BENEFITS IS VALID. THEIR DUTIES INCLUDE THE

DETERMINATION OF WHETHER A GIVEN INJURY AROSE OUT OF THE SCOPE OF EMPLOYMENT OR THE DETERMINATION OF THE DEGREE OF INJURY WHERE DISPUTES EXIST.

